{"title":"Pro Log: Evenepoel returns; Underdogs win Amstel Gold Race; Ciccone fined for yeet; Vos signs lifetime deal; Barry Hoban dies","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/pro-cycling-news-2025-amstel-gold","date":1745338922000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/pro-cycling-news-2025-amstel-gold\">Pro Log: Evenepoel returns; Underdogs win Amstel Gold Race; Ciccone fined for yeet; Vos signs lifetime deal; Barry Hoban dies</a></p>\n\n<p>Welcome back to another edition of <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/pro-log\" target=\"_blank\">Pro Log</a>. Here’s a rundown of the latest results before we get started:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Stage 2, Tour of the Alps, Tues 22nd April:</strong> 1st Michael Storer, Tudor Pro Cycling, 5hr 00min 02sec; 2nd Paul Seixas, Decathlon AG2R La Mondiale, +41sec; 3rd Romain Bardet, Team Picnic PostNL, +41sec.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Stage 1, Tour of the Alps, Mon 21st April: </strong>1st Giulio Ciccone, Lidl-Trek, 3h 42min 10sec; 2nd Felix Gall, Decathlon AG2R La Mondiale, +0sec; 3rd Paul Seixas, Decathlon AG2R La Mondiale, +0sec.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Ronde de Mouscron, Mon 21st April: </strong>1st Susanne Andersen, Uno-X Mobility, 3h 02min 14sec; 2nd Marthe Truyven, Fenix-Deceuninck, +0sec; 3rd Sarah van Dam, Ceratizit Pro Cycling, +0sec.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Men’s Amstel Gold Race, Sun 20th April: </strong>1st Mattias Skjelmose, Lidl-Trek, 5h 49min 58sec; 2nd Tadej Pogačar, UAE Team Emirates XRG, +0sec; 3rd Remco Evenepoel, Soudal Quick-Step, +0sec.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Women’s Amstel Gold Race, Sun 20th April: </strong>1st Mischa Bredewold, SD Worx-Protime, 4h 03min 03sec; 2nd Ellen van Dijk, Lidl-Trek, +07sec; 3rd Puck Pieterse, Fenix-Deceuninck, +07sec.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>Remco Evenepoel is back like he never left</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"970\" height=\"645\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2210883852-970x645.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2210883852-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2210883852-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2210883852-768x511.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2210883852-1536x1021.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2210883852-2048x1362.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2210883852-750x499.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2210883852-1140x758.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2210883852-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2210883852-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2210883852-350x233.webp 350w\" /><figcaption>Rhode Van Elsen/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Remco Evenepoel came out swinging on his return to the peloton after a tough off-season injured. Breaking away with Wout van Aert at Brabantse Pijl, the Olympic road race champion upset the odds by beating his compatriot in the sprint finish for his first victory since the World Championship time-trial in September.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It was another case of close but no cigar for Van Aert. In the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/all-you-need-to-know-about-the-classics-monuments-cobbles\">Classics </a>so far this season, he has finished second twice – having lost sprints to Evenepoel and Neilson Powless – and just off the podium in fourth at the Ronde van Vlaanderen, Paris-Roubaix and the Amstel Gold Race.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Still, it was great to see the respect between Van Aert and Evenepoel after the finish.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions?utm_source=Web&amp;utm_medium=Banner&amp;utm_campaign=Banner+4\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-970x300.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-970x300.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-300x93.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-768x238.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-1536x476.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-2048x634.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-750x232.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Subs-flash-163-for-web-4-1140x353.webp 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Mischa Bredewold and Mattias Skjelmose win the Amstel Gold Race</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1752\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2211107448-scaled.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2211107448-scaled.webp 2560w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2211107448-300x205.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2211107448-970x664.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2211107448-768x525.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2211107448-1536x1051.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2211107448-2048x1401.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2211107448-750x513.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2211107448-1140x780.webp 1140w\" /><figcaption>Luc Claessen/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>SD Worx-Protime’s Mischa Bredewold took her first victory of the year and the biggest of her career at the Amstel Gold Race. Puck Pieterse set a fierce pace on the Geulhemmerberg to help splinter the race alongside French champion Juliette Labous. They were soon joined by UAE’s Silvia Persico with Lidl-Trek’s Ellen van Dijk and Bredewold then bridging a few kilometres afterwards.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Bredewold followed an attack by Van Dijk in the final 6km and jumped clear on the last climb up the Cauberg but remained in the sight of the chasing group, her gap only a handful of seconds in the last kilometre. Despite being a dangling carrot, she managed to hold on to take the victory.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the men’s race, Mattias Skjelmose also claimed the biggest victory of his career in a dramatic sprint finish against Tadej Pogačar and Evenepoel after Pogačar’s solo move was successfully chased down.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There was a brief wait after the line for confirmation that he had indeed beaten the two giants – a video shared by Lidl-Trek sees him repeating the phrase ‘I think I won… I think I won…’ He was finally given the all-clear to celebrate and, after a few pre-watershed F-bombs, he dedicated the victory to his grandfather who passed away last month.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/100-wins-club\">How significant is joining the 100 wins club?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/tour-of-britain-women-2025-route\">From Yorkshire to Glasgow: Tour of Britain Women 2025 route revealed</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/which-riders-deserve-a-lifetime-contract\">Wout’s World: Which other pro riders deserve lifetime contracts?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/yorkshire-gold-barry-hoban-profile\">Yorkshire gold: Remembering Barry Hoban 1940-2025</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/all-you-need-to-know-about-the-classics-monuments-cobbles\">Cycling Spring Classics 2025: Race dates, Monuments, cobbles and live TV guide</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Giulio Ciccone fined for celebration</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div></div><img width=\"970\" height=\"676\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2211273453-970x676.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2211273453-970x676.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2211273453-300x209.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2211273453-768x535.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2211273453-1536x1070.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2211273453-2048x1427.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2211273453-750x522.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/GettyImages-2211273453-1140x794.webp 1140w\" /><figcaption>Tim de Waele/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s been a long time since we’ve seen Giulio Ciccone’s trademark celebration of throwing away his sunglasses. It’s a move he started at the 2019 Giro d’Italia and followed up at the 2022 race, and the Italian once again launched his 100% sunnies into the crowd after winning the opening stage of the Tour of the Alps.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, he was later fined 250 Swiss francs and docked 15 UCI points for supposedly damaging the image of the sport. But for the child who picked them up? Priceless.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Marianne Vos signs lifetime contract with Visma</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Adobe-Express-file-37-970x647.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Adobe-Express-file-37-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Adobe-Express-file-37-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Adobe-Express-file-37-768x512.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Adobe-Express-file-37-1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Adobe-Express-file-37-750x500.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Adobe-Express-file-37-1140x760.webp 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Adobe-Express-file-37-465x310.webp 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Adobe-Express-file-37-620x413.webp 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Adobe-Express-file-37-350x233.webp 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Adobe-Express-file-37.webp 1800w\" /><figcaption>A.S.O./Thomas Maheux</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Marianne Vos has signed a new contract with Visma-Lease a Bike until the end of her career, whenever that may be. Describing the team as ‘like home’, Vos has been with Visma since 2021 and in that time has worn the yellow jersey and won the green jersey at the Tour de France Femmes, topped the points classification at La Vuelta Femenina, won more national and world championships in cyclocross and claimed a maiden world title in gravel. In 2023, she notched her 250th career win at Dwars door Vlaanderen and shows no signs of slowing down.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the greatest cyclists the sport has ever seen, she’s now the second rider that Visma-Lease a Bike have given <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/which-riders-deserve-a-lifetime-contract\" target=\"_blank\">a lifetime contract</a> after Wout van Aert.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tom Pidcock wins at Laureus Awards</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/Tom-Pidcock-wins-gold-2024-Olympics-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/Tom-Pidcock-wins-gold-2024-Olympics-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/Tom-Pidcock-wins-gold-2024-Olympics-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/Tom-Pidcock-wins-gold-2024-Olympics-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/Tom-Pidcock-wins-gold-2024-Olympics-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/Tom-Pidcock-wins-gold-2024-Olympics-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/Tom-Pidcock-wins-gold-2024-Olympics-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/Tom-Pidcock-wins-gold-2024-Olympics-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/Tom-Pidcock-wins-gold-2024-Olympics-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/Tom-Pidcock-wins-gold-2024-Olympics-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/07/Tom-Pidcock-wins-gold-2024-Olympics-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption> Alex Broadway/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Tom Pidcock won the Action Sportsperson of the Year Award at the Laureus World Sports Awards. In a category that crowned BMXer Beth Shriever as victor in 2022, Pidcock won for his achievements at the Olympics where he defended his title in the mountain bike race. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Barry Hoban dies aged 85</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2019/02/04221613/barry_hoban_profile_12-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"barry_hoban_profile_12\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2019/02/04221613/barry_hoban_profile_12-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2019/02/04221613/barry_hoban_profile_12-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2019/02/04221613/barry_hoban_profile_12-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2019/02/04221613/barry_hoban_profile_12-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2019/02/04221613/barry_hoban_profile_12-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2019/02/04221613/barry_hoban_profile_12-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2019/02/04221613/barry_hoban_profile_12-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2019/02/04221613/barry_hoban_profile_12-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2019/02/04221613/barry_hoban_profile_12.jpg 2000w\" /><figcaption>Joe McGorty / Cyclist</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>British cycling legend Barry Hoban died this weekend aged 85. The Wakefield man won eight stages of the Tour de France between 1967 and 1975, his first an honorary win following the death of his Great Britain teammate Tom Simpson the day before.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In his professional racing career he rode mostly for the iconic Mercier team alongside Raymond Poulidor. Alongside his Tour exploits, Hoban helped Simpson win the 1965 Worlds, won two stages of the Vuelta and won the 1974 Gent-Wevelgem, where he beat Roger De Vlaeminck and Eddy Merckx. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Read <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/yorkshire-gold-barry-hoban-profile\">our 2014 profile of Barry Hoban: Yorkshire gold</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>See you next week.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/newsletters\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"351\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-3-970x351.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-3-970x351.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-3-300x109.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-3-768x278.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-3-1536x556.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-3-2048x741.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-3-750x271.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-3-1140x412.jpg 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/pro-cycling-news-2025-amstel-gold\">Pro Log: Evenepoel returns; Underdogs win Amstel Gold Race; Ciccone fined for yeet; Vos signs lifetime deal; Barry Hoban dies</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Robyn Davidson &#124; Editorial Assistant","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"7309b5e9adc5a5f1a3af41095cd798da58d8166204e72f5d61c6d2cad4f20a2e","category":"Cycling"}